Context("Numeric");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

# f(x) = 2x^3-2x^2+1

$a = random(2,5,1);
$b = $a + 2;
$b++ if ( 3*$a*$x0*$x0 - 2*$b*$x0 == 0 );

$c = random(1,15,1);
$x0 = random(1,3,1);
$y0 = $a*($x0**3) - $b*$x0*$x0 + $c;
$func = "$a x^3 - $b x^2 + $c";

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Find the equation of the line tangent to the graph of \( f \) at
\( ($x0,$y0) \), where \( f \) is given by
\( f(x)= $func \).

$PAR
\( y = \) \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

$m = 3*$a*$x0*$x0 - 2*$b*$x0;

ANS(Compute( "$m*(x-$x0) + $y0" )->cmp() );

$threea = 3*$a;
$twob = 2*$b;
$fpx0 = $m;

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

Differentiating gives
\( f'(x) = $threea x^2 - $twob x \), so
\( f'($x0) = $m \).  Thus the equation of the tangent line is 
\( y - $y0 = $m ( x - $x0 ) \), or
\( y = $y0 + $m (x - $x0 ) \).

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


